---
import PageLayout from '../components/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Read a Sample - Burning Down the House">
	<h1>Read a Sample</h1>
	
	<p>This page will contain an excerpt from the book, allowing readers to preview the content before purchasing. The sample will be substantial enough to give a genuine sense of the work's style and substance.</p>

	<div class="sample-content">
		<h2>Chapter One</h2>
		
		<p>Placeholder text for the sample chapter will appear here. The excerpt will be formatted exactly as it appears in the book, maintaining the same typography and layout principles.</p>

		<p>The sample will be long enough to provide a meaningful preview, typically several pages or a complete chapter section. Readers will be able to assess the quality and style of the writing before making a purchase decision.</p>

		<p>This preview serves as a demonstration of the book's approach, tone, and intellectual rigor. It will be representative of the work as a whole, giving potential readers an accurate sense of what to expect.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="actions">
		<a href="/buy" class="button">Buy the Book</a>
	</div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
	.sample-content {
		margin: 3rem 0;
	}

	.actions {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.button {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		background-color: #1a1a1a;
		color: #faf8f5;
		border: none;
		padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
		cursor: pointer;
		text-decoration: none;
		display: inline-block;
		transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
	}

	.button:hover {
		opacity: 0.85;
	}
</style>
